fields.description:
While decommissioning some datanodes, we observed OP_READ_BLOCK failures from DFSClient instances.  Tracing back the history in the logs reveals that the DFSClient instance was started after the block in question had been migrated off the DataNode that was being accessed at the time of the OP_READ_BLOCK failure.  It appears that the NameNode, despite having orchestrated the migration of the data, continued to provide a DataNode as a valid source of a block, despite it no longer being present.

Timeline:

The DN deleted the block at 09:43:20.
The DFSClient instance was started at 09:46:33.

DFS Client Error was:
